  "local_port": 52406,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the recipes of five minutes easy to make snacks?",
  "response": "Here are a few simple and quick snack recipes that you can whip up in about five minutes:\n\n1. **Peanut Butter and Banana Rice Cakes**:\n   - Ingredients: Rice cakes, peanut butter, banana, honey (optional).\n   - Instructions: Spread peanut butter on a rice cake, slice a banana on top, and drizzle with honey if desired.\n\n2. **Caprese Skewers**:\n   - Ingredients: Cherry tomatoes, mozzarella balls, fresh basil leaves, balsamic glaze.\n   - Instructions: On small skewers, alternate threading cherry tomatoes, mozzarella balls, and basil leaves. Drizzle with balsamic glaze.\n\n3. **Avocado Toast**:\n   - Ingredients: Bread, ripe avocado, salt, pepper, red pepper flakes (optional), lemon juice.\n   - Instructions: Toast the bread. Mash the avocado with a fork, add salt, pepper, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Spread on the toast and top with red pepper flakes if desired.\n\n4. **Greek Yogurt Parfait**:\n   - Ingredients: Greek yogurt, granola, mixed berries, honey.\n   - Instructions: Layer Greek yogurt with granola and mixed berries in a glass or bowl. Drizzle with honey.\n\n5. **Apple and Cheese Sandwich**:\n   - Ingredients: Apple slices, cheddar cheese slices, whole grain bread.\n   - Instructions: Place cheddar cheese and apple slices between two slices of bread. Use a sandwich press or simply eat as is.\n\n6. **Hummus and Veggie Wrap**:\n   - Ingredients: Whole wheat tortilla, hummus, sliced bell peppers, spinach leaves.\n   - Instructions: Spread hummus on the tortilla, place bell pepper slices and spinach leaves, then roll it up tightly.\n\n7. **Chocolate-Dipped Pretzels**:\n   - Ingredients: Pretzel rods, chocolate chips.\n   - Instructions: Melt chocolate chips in the microwave in intervals, dip pretzel rods halfway into the chocolate, and let them cool on a parchment-lined sheet.\n\n8. **Cucumber Sandwiches**:\n   - Ingredients: Cucumber slices, cream cheese, dill (optional), bread or crackers.\n   - Instructions: Spread cream cheese on bread or crackers, top with cucumber slices, and sprinkle with dill if desired.\n\nThese snacks are both versatile and quick, perfect for when you need a swift and satisfying bite!",
